data.content:
## What breaks: Sync I/O on Cosmos DB is **fully removed** in EF Core 11

In .NET 10 you could opt back into sync-over-async with `CosmosOptionsExtension`. In .NET 11, **that opt-in no longer exists** — calling any synchronous API always throws. Every method in your repository is affected.

### Required fix — convert to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key mapping:** `ToList()` → `ToListAsync()`, `First()` → `FirstAsync()`, `Count()` → `CountAsync()`, `SaveChanges()` → `SaveChangesAsync()`.

This will cascade — all callers of these methods must also become `async`/`await` up the call chain (controllers, services, etc.). Also note a second Cosmos change: **empty owned collections** now return an empty collection instead of `null`, so update any `is null` checks on owned collections.
